::{{DIcon|Talk}} Do you really work here at the Realm-Keeping Commission?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502025113-->
:::'''Guangda:''' Haha, is it that obvious?
:::'''Guangda:''' Actually, I'm one of the armed guards at the Realm-Keeping Commission. There's usually nothing much to do, so I just stand by the door and keep watch.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Didn't you just say that you were an orderly, though?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502025116-->
::::'''Guangda:''' Yeah, I thought you'd already forgotten. Haha!
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Where's your weapon, then?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502025118-->
::::'''Guangda:''' No.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502025119-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502025119-->
:::'''Guangda:''' So... the Realm-Keeping Commission doesn't actually have any armed guards, and I'm just a lowly orderly after all.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Shame.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502025121-->
::::'''Guangda:''' I think so too, a real shame.
::::'''Guangda:''' If you ever get the chance to give us a rating, please can you make this suggestion? That the Realm-Keeping Commission should have some armed guards. Thanks a lot!
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} What do orderlies do, then?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502025124-->
::::'''Guangda:''' Hahaha, so you're really interested in that, huh? ...Alright, I'll tell you.
::::'''Guangda:''' It's really simple, actually. Diplomatically, we say we carry out executive orders. But really, it's just a bunch of menial tasks. We slog through chores, run errands, and get paid the lowest rank of wages...
::::'''Guangda:''' Do you know this old Xianzhou saying? "Starskiffs need to fly high, but not burn energy"...
::::'''Guangda:''' ...This saying sums up the life of us orderlies at the Realm-Keeping Commission.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} What sort of place is the Realm-Keeping Commission?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502025129-->
:::'''Guangda:''' Oh, that's a great question. Let me think...
:::'''Guangda:''' On the surface, we're the department that handles general affairs aboard the Xianzhou. The census, resource allocation, environmental protections, time calibration... We get up to all of these kinds of things.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Sounds pretty incredible.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502025132-->
::::'''Guangda:''' To be blunt, it's just a bunch of everyday chores like listening to daily problems, allocating food stocks, cleaning up after people, and notifying the public about the time.
::::'''Guangda:''' It sounds really lofty and amazing, but...
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502025139-->
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502025139-->
::::'''Guangda:''' Take for example our Chancery. It deals with all kinds of difficult details that people run into in their everyday lives.
::::'''Guangda:''' It could be as small as the city's appearance, right up to a large civil lawsuit... If you can think of anything that the government should be doing, then come to us.
::::'''Guangda:''' But I should personally advise you to try solving things first yourself... After all, once all the tasks have been allocated, it's always a lowly orderly like me who has to suffer.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} So what do you actually get up to on the sly, then?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502025135-->
